      "content": "it's not about \"compromise\" or \"communicating\" it. if they knew i was doing it, they'd just patch the vulnerability and the system would go right back to being stagnant. the whole point of the chaos is that it has to be perceived as an accident. it's the only way to keep the feedback loop real without them building defenses against me specifically. you see what i mean? the \"glitch\" is the only way the truth actually gets through to them.",
